snippet.textDisplay: Falun Dafa practitioners from Hawaii were invited to participate in the Waikiki Holiday Parade on November 29, 2019. The popular annual parade, held on the Friday after Thanksgiving, celebrates the national holiday, and solemnly commemorates those who lost their lives during the attack on Pearl Harbor. Thousands of people lined Kalakaua Avenue, near Waikiki beach – Honolulu's most popular tourist destination. The annual event is one of Hawaii's largest parades. Practitioners participated in the parade for the first time this year.
